{"word":"H2556 - חָמֵץ - châmêts - khaw-mates' - Cruel","slug":"H2556","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָמֵץ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châmêts"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-mates'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cruel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05DE;&#x05E5; - cha&#x0302;me&#x0302;ts</b> - <i>khaw-mates'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be pungent</i>; that is, in taste (<i>sour</i>, that is, literally <i>fermented</i>, or figuratively <i>harsh</i>), in color (<i>dazzling</i>): - cruel (man), dyed, be grieved, leavened."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2541\">H2541</a>"}]}